The paper deals with the design and analysis of binary constrained codes for bipolar non-return-to-zero signaling, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The codes are also applicable in magnetic recording (MR) devices, Flash devices, and optical recording devices, which are areas of interest in distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the circuit complexity of the codes, which is a topic in electronic engineering (cs.ET).
